  description : "JUEX-L2-000150 - The Juniper EX switch must be configured to enable Storm Control on all host-facing access interfaces."
  info        : "A traffic storm occurs when packets flood a LAN, creating excessive traffic and degrading network performance. Traffic storm control prevents network disruption by suppressing ingress traffic when the number of packets reaches configured threshold levels. Traffic storm control monitors ingress traffic levels on a port and drops traffic when the number of packets reaches the configured threshold level during any one-second interval.

